# Environment Setup

This Cursor workspace has two folder trees loaded simultaneously:
- `AI-Dex` — personal knowledge vault (Dex)
- `Cognome AI-workspace` — Cognome product and client work

## AI Environments in Use

Two AI environments operate in this workspace:
- Claude Code (Cursor plugin)
- Cursor agentic chat (offers a selection of agents: Composer, Claude, ChatGPT, etc.)

Both should follow the same rules and guidelines.

## Single Source of Truth

**CLAUDE.md files are the source of truth for all rules and guidelines.**

- `C:\Users\chris\OneDrive\AI-Dex\CLAUDE.md` — Dex vault rules
- `C:\Users\chris\OneDrive\Documents\PPM Career\Clients & Startups\Cognome\AI-workspace\CLAUDE.md` — Cognome workspace rules

The `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files are thin delegates that point to the relevant CLAUDE.md section. They do NOT contain the actual rules.

## Rule: When Editing Rules or Guidelines

1. Edit the relevant CLAUDE.md file first — that is the only place rules live
2. Do NOT edit `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files to add or change rule content
3. Only touch `.mdc` files if you need Cursor-specific behavior that does not belong in CLAUDE.md (rare)

This ensures all three AI environments stay in sync automatically.
